Symptomatic vertebral hemangioma: the treatment of 23 cases and a review of the literature. It is the purpose of this study to analyze a group of 23 patients affected with hemangioma in one or more metameres of the vertebral column. On the basis of clinical examination and instrumental testing in time (minimum follow-up 12 months, maximum 217 months) the following treatment options are discussed: medical treatment and clinical monitoring closer in time palliative surgical treatment whether or not associated with embolization of vascular afferences of the lesion and adjuvant treatment